## Resources

### `AssistantMessageResource`
```json
{
  "id": "hash",
  "role": "user|assistant|system",
  "content": "...",
  "channel": "web|whatsapp",
  "actions": [],
  "metadata": {},
  "created_at": "ISO8601"
}
```

### `ConversationResource`
```json
{
  "id": "hash",
  "session_id": "hash",
  "created_at": "ISO8601"
}
```

---

## Multimodal — MIMEs aceptados

| Tipo | MIMEs |
|---|---|
| Audio | `audio/mpeg`, `audio/ogg`, `audio/webm` |
| Imagen | `image/jpeg`, `image/png`, `image/webp` |
| Documento | `application/pdf` |

El adjunto se sube via Spatie Media Library al bucket S3 antes de llamar al endpoint.

---

## Frontend — guard de ruta `/app/assistant`

El router verifica que el enterprise activo (`X-Enterprise-ID` en uso) sea de tipo `personal`.
Si no lo es → redirige a `/switch/` y lanza toast:

```
"Para usar el Asistente debes cambiar a tu cuenta personal."
```

---

## Docker — worker dedicado `queue-assistant`

```yaml
queue-assistant:
  build:
    context: .
    dockerfile: docker/queue/Dockerfile
  command: ["php", "artisan", "queue:work", "--queue=assistant"]
  env_file: ./backend/.env
  depends_on:
    php:
      condition: service_healthy
  networks:
    - backend
  restart: unless-stopped
```

El servicio `queue` existente no debe incluir la cola `assistant`.

